MANY years after COVID-19 attacked the world, The Ibejii Live Experience (TILX) is back. The Ibejii Live Experience, according to The double British/Nigerian Afro-soul singer, and composer, Ibejii, the event will return with the first show at Terra Kulture on July 10.   AVRS, NCC meet stakeholders in Lagos     All eyes are on Nigeria, we must do better, says Sleek     My moniker means I was sent by laughter, says Eze   Ibejii, a nominee at the Headies is expected to serenade fans with an Afro-soul sound that speaks to love, life, societal ills, etc. Gonto, one of the songs to be performed at the live experience, is the first single by the singer to receive a nomination for a 2022 Headies Award in the category of Best Alternative Song. The second nomination, ‘Intermission’ is in the category of Best Alternative Album. The six-track album is a collection of songs with themes about the issues faced by Nigerian youth. With TILX: The Phoenix, Ibejii returns to belt out songs from his wide catalog, including songs from the newly released Post-19, a 7-track album released in celebration of life.